The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Scientist dead
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      Scientist dead
                            
	Bhopal, April 11: A young scientist working for the Raja Ramanna Centre for Advanced Technology in Indore was found hanging at his house last night in a suspected suicide, after apparently leaving a note that accused a superior of mental torture.        
	Police today booked the senior, G.S. Lodha, for abetting the alleged suicide.        
	Tirumala Prasad Tenkas body was first noticed by his domestic help in a decomposed state when she entered his house yesterday.                                                                                                                                                           
